entry.content:
When a TestSuite test runs, but the ICU data loading fails, none of the test run, but the binary exits with a code of `0`.

This is due to a return code of `0` (which is implicitly cast from `false`) in `RunTestSuite()` in [unit_test_launcher.cc](https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:base/test/launcher/unit_test_launcher.cc;l=187;drc=67abccd5637d298295794961f248a9ef5c20bbbc).

```
  // ICU must be initialized before any attempts to format times, e.g. for logs.
  if (!base::i18n::InitializeICU()) {
    return false;
  }
```

If the failure to initialize ICU is fatal, then the return value should be non-zero.

This was noticed when diagnosing an issue with some ChromeOS unit tests: b/327258234.

**OS**: Linux

**Chrome build number**: 122.0.6261.69 (Official Build) (64-bit)

